======================================================================
LEAD 1: H(T) = # VALID ORDERINGS OF A COMPARISON NETWORK
  A tournament IS a comparison network where each comparison is resolved.
  H counts the consistent total orderings = the 'answers' the network admits.
  Connection: sorting network complexity theory!
======================================================================
  Transitive tournament: H=1 = deterministic sort
  Regular tournament: max H = most ambiguous comparator
  H measures the 'entropy' of the sorting network's output

