======================================================================
LEAD 3: PERMANENT-DETERMINANT-H TRINITY
  perm(A) = cycle covers, det(A) = signed cycle covers, H = paths
  These are three 'evaluations' of the adjacency matrix
======================================================================
  bits=0: H=1, det=0, perm=0
  bits=42: H=13, det=2, perm=2
  bits=511: H=1, det=0, perm=0
  bits=1023: H=1, det=0, perm=0

  H is a 'path permanent': sum over perms of CONSECUTIVE products
  perm is a 'cycle permanent': sum over perms of DIAGONAL products
  det is a signed version of perm

