LEAD 10: TOURNAMENT AS QUANTUM STATE
  |T> = (1/sqrt(N)) sum_bits |bits> in the Hilbert space C^N
  H = <T| H_op |T> where H_op is the Hamiltonian path operator
  The eigenvalues of H_op are the possible H values
======================================================================
  At n=5: N=1024, #eigenvalues of H_op = #distinct H = 7
  H_op has rank 7 in the H-eigenbasis

======================================================================
LEAD 11: FORBIDDEN H VALUES AND SPECIAL NUMBERS
======================================================================
  Permanent gaps: H=[7, 21]
  7 = 2^3 - 1 (Mersenne prime)
  21 = 3 * 7 = |Phi+(A6)|
  63 = 2^6 - 1 (Mersenne) — NOT permanently forbidden (achievable at n=8)
  The (z-2)(z-3) recurrence: z=3 orbit from seed 7: 7, 21, 63, 189, ...
  189 = 3^3 * 7 = max H at n=7 (NOT forbidden!)
  The forbidden sequence STOPS: 7 and 21 are forbidden, but 63 is not.
  The 'escape' happens at n=8 where alpha_3 >= 1 kicks in.

